                  addition, the new paradigm enhances the security of
                  the original signature scheme since it is only used
                  to sign random strings chosen off-line by the
                  signer. This makes the converted scheme secure
                  against adaptive chosen message attacks even if the
                  original scheme is secure only against generic
                  chosen message attacks or against random message
                  attacks.},
