                  SPEKE is more or less DH-EKE \cite{BelMer92,STW95a} 
                  except that the password is not used to encrypt the
                  residues but to generate the base as a generator of
                  the (prime) order $q$ multiplicative subgroup
                  of a prime order $p$ group used for the
                  DH-exponentiations. Two examples are proposed:
                  $g=S^{p-1/q}$ or $g={g'}^S$ with $S$ the password and
                  $g'$ a generator of the subgroup. 
