  year = 		 2000,
  number =		 2,
  month =		 aug,
  abstract =	 {Secure group communication is an increasingly popular research area
having received much attention in the last several years. The
fundamental challenge revolves around secure and efficient group key
management. While centralized methods are often appropriate for key
distribution in large groups, many collaborative group settings
require distributed key agreement techniques. This work investigates a
novel approach to group key agreement by blending binary key trees
